\b Programs:
\b0 \
qemu-system-ppc is a PowerPC Macintosh emulator.\
qemu-system-x86_64 is a 64-bit PC emulator.\
qemu-system-i386 is a 32-bit PC emulator.\
qemu-img is an image file creation program.\
\
This package comes with the above emulators all at version 2.10.1. It is mainly to be used from the terminal program that comes with Mac OS X. \
\

\b Command-line:
\b0 \
Running the emulator:\
qemu-system-i386 -m <memory size for emulator> -hda <hard drive image file> -cdrom <cdrom image file> -boot <boot drive> -soundhw <sound card> ...\
\
Creating an image file for the emulator's hard drive:\
qemu-img create -f qcow2 <name>.qcow2 <size in GB>G\
\
Examples:\
./qemu-system-i386 -m 400 -hda ReactOSHD.qcow2 -boot c -soundhw ac97 -net nic,model=ne2k_pci -net user\
\
qemu-img create -f qcow2 ReactOSHD.qcow2 1G\
\
./qemu-system-ppc -m 256 -M mac99 -hda "Mac OS 9 HD.img\'94 -cdrom doom.iso -boot c \
\

\b Files:
\b0 \
Programs folder - stores all the usable programs\
pc-bios - bios files for the emulator\
libs - library files used by the programs\
\
This program is made to be portable. All the files need to stay together in order for these programs to work.\
\
Please see http://qemu.org for more information.\
\

\b System Requirements:
\b0 \
64-bit x86 processor\
Mac OS 10.6 or higher\
\

